{"type":"message","id":"bfeb5f8c","parentId":"f5467e39","timestamp":"2026-05-02T15:50:10.925Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the picture clearly:\n\n**Memory pressure details:**\n- System has 8GB RAM total (8589934592 bytes = 8GB)\n- **Pages free: 40140** (only ~620MB free)\n- **Pages purgeable: 343** (almost nothing available to purge)\n- **Swap: HUGE** — Swapins: 283M, Swapouts: 305M — the system is heavily swapping\n- **Pages active: 98865**, **Pages wired: 127076** — lots of memory in use\n- **Compressor: 119565 pages** being used by compressor — memory is being compressed\n\n\n- **System-wide memory free: 49%** but that's misleading because so much is being swapped and compressed\n\nThe real issue is that OpenClaw's gateway is using 5.6% of memory (472MB) with 14.7% CPU, which isn't unusually high, but there are multiple Chrome Helper processes running alongside the WindowServer at 53.9% CPU and Telegram at 26.4% CPU. The sheer volume of background processes combined with aggressive swapping suggests the system is memory-constrained despite the percentage appearing reasonable.\n\nI should check the cron jobs to see if there are any stuck processes causing the slowdown, and look at the OpenClaw configuration to understand what's actually running.\n","thinkingSignature":"7b5b1044dea7c1aab379a22760fdc377068060486290a4ed81d0d420626da6a9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_i5g713a8y49v_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"http://127.0.0.1:18789/health\" 2>&1 || echo \"Gateway health check failed\"","timeout":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_i5g713a8y49v_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw status 2>&1 | head -60","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3394,"output":380,"cacheRead":47424,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51198,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopRea