{"type":"message","id":"b41f5b6a","parentId":"14be2dbe","timestamp":"2026-05-02T15:51:37.622Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me analyze what's happening:\n\n**System state:**\n- 8GB RAM, 49% free — actually not terrible\n- Swap: 283M swapins, 305M swapouts — HEAVY swap usage\n- CPU: ~22% idle, mostly idle — not the bottleneck\n- OpenClaw Gateway is at 14.7% CPU and 5.6% RAM — running hot but not crisis\n- 473 processes, 6 stuck — WindowServer at 53.9% CPU\n\n**The main issues:**\n\n1. **Too many active cron jobs hammering the system:**\n   - MC Watchdog (cron:4a07) — runs every 5 minutes, sends a message every time\n   - Weather Cache (cron:7207) — runs every 15 minutes, also sends to Telegram\n   - That's a Telegram message literally every 3-4 minutes, 24/7\n   - Plus the Zyrtec reminder at 9 PM, Flonase at 9 AM, Weekly cleanup, Morning Brief at 5:30 AM\n\n2. **Memory pressure from swap thrashing** — 283M swapins and 305M swapouts indicates the system is constantly paging. The 8GB MacBook Air is being asked to do too much.\n\n3. **WindowServer at 53.9% CPU** — This is unusual. Could be a runaway UI process or Chrome tab.\n\n4. **OpenClaw is using 14.7% CPU + 5.6% RAM** — That's significant for a background service, but it's Node.js doing a lot of work (cron jobs, agent sessions, LLM calls).\n\n5. **Too many active sessions** — Main, Emmy, Rex, plus subagents. All using token windows.\n\n**Recommendations for Bobby:**\n\n1. **Reduce MC Watchdog frequency** — It's sending \"✅ MC OK\" every 5 minutes. That's noise. Change it to every 30 min or disable.\n2. **Reduce Weather Cache pings** — 15 min is fine but if it's slow, bump to 30 min.\n\n\n3. **Look at what's consuming WindowServer resources** — Close unnecessary Chrome tabs and other UI processes that are driving up CPU usage.\n4. **Consolidate or eliminate redundant cron jobs** — Several are firing too frequently and creating unnecessary load.\n5. **Check memory usage more systematically** — The swap thrashing suggests RAM is being overcommitted, which could be fixed by reducing background processes.\n\nLet me give Bobby a clear, structured diagnosis and fixes.\n","thinkingSignature":"43df02d9da4b1a0ca9a23db7a184cb34058262e33e813023245867f53003c5af"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nHere's the diagnosis. Your MacBook Air (8GB) is being asked to do **way too much**, and it's swapping heavily — that's what's causing the slowness.\n\n**The culprits:**\n\n**1. Too many cron jobs firing constantly:**\n- **MC Watchdog** — sends \"✅ MC OK\" to Telegram **every 5 minutes, 24/7** — that's ~288 messages per DAY just saying \"everything's fine\"\n- **Weather Cache** — every 15 min\n- **Emmy Email Check** — every hour\n- **Heartbeat** — every 30 min\n- Plus reminders, morning brief, etc.\n\nThat's a message to Telegram every 3-4 minutes *in the background* while OpenClaw is also running agents and LLM calls.\n\n**2. Heavy memory pressure:**\n- 283M swapins / 305M swapouts — your 8GB is constantly paging\n- OpenClaw gateway alone is using 5.6% RAM + 14.7% CPU\n- WindowServer is at 53.9% CPU (unusual — something in the UI layer is struggling)\n\n**3. Too many active sessions:** Main, Emmy, Rex, and subagents all keeping large token contexts alive.\n\n**What we can fix right now:**\n\n| Job | Current | Change to |\n|-----|---------|-----------|\n| MC Watchdog | Every 5 min | **Every 30 min** or disable |\n| Weather Cache | Every 15 min | Every 30 min |\n| Heartbeat | Every 30 min | Every 60 min |\n| Emmy Email | Every hour | Leave as-is |\n\nWant me to:\n1. **Reduce the watchdog frequency** — it's mostly noise\n2. **Check for any stuck Chrome tabs** causing WindowServer pressure  \n3. **Trim session sizes** to reduce memory load\n\nThese won't fix the hardware limit, but they'll reduce the constant load and make everything feel snappier. The 8GB MacBook Air was never meant to run a full AI team 24/7 — we need to be smarter about when things run."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":31773,"output":969,"cacheRead":51648,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84390,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777737062649,"responseId":"06455067c30c230980b84aebb5b762f6"}}
