{"type":"message","id":"a0fe0f18","parentId":"5fa5a113","timestamp":"2026-05-02T15:55:19.408Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2ytwjjm8eole_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC \"-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN\" \"http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd\">\n<plist version=\"1.0\">\n<dict>\n    <key>Label</key>\n    <string>com.bobby.missioncontrol.vite</string>\n    <key>ProgramArguments</key>\n    <array>\n        <string>/bin/bash</string>\n        <string>-c</string>\n        <string>export PATH=\"/opt/homebrew/opt/node/bin:/opt/homebrew/bin:/usr/local/bin:/bin:/usr/bin\"; cd /Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control; /opt/homebrew/bin/node /Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/node_modules/vite/bin/vite.js --port 8787 --host</string>\n    </array>\n    <key>RunAtLoad</key>\n    <true/>\n    <key>KeepAlive</key>\n    <dict>\n        <key>SuccessfulExit</key>\n        <false/>\n    </dict>\n    <key>StandardOutPath</key>\n    <string>/tmp/mc-vite-launchd.log</string>\n    <key>StandardErrorPath</key>\n    <string>/tmp/mc-vite-launchd.log</string>\n</dict>\n</plist>"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":11,"aggregated":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC \"-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN\" \"http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd\">\n<plist version=\"1.0\">\n<dict>\n    <key>Label</key>\n    <string>com.bobby.missioncontrol.vite</string>\n    <key>ProgramArguments</key>\n    <array>\n        <string>/bin/bash</string>\n        <string>-c</string>\n        <string>export PATH=\"/opt/homebrew/opt/node/bin:/opt/homebrew/bin:/usr/local/bin:/bin:/usr/bin\"; cd /Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control; /opt/homebrew/bin/node /Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/node_modules/vite/bin/vite.js --port 8787 --host</string>\n    </array>\n    <key>RunAtLoad</key>\n    <true/>\n    <key>KeepAlive</key>\n    <dict>\n        <key>SuccessfulExit</key>\n        <false/>\n    </dict>\n    <key>StandardOutPath</key>\n    <string>/tmp/mc-vite-launchd.log</string>\n    <key>StandardErrorPath</key>\n    <string>/tmp/mc-vite-launchd.log</string>\n</dict>\n</plist>","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777737319408}}
{"type":"message","id":"cc305788","parentId":"a0fe0f18","timestamp":"2026-05-02T15:55:46.342Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the Mission Control services are running:\n1. API server on some port (not 3001 or 8787 apparently - 3001 doesn't seem to be running based on earlier check)\n2. Vite dev server on port 8787\n\nWait, port 8787 shows a Vite server but earlier I got an HTML response from it. Let me check again.\n\nActually earlier: `curl -s http://127.0.0.1:8787` returned `<!doctype html>` which means the Vite server IS running on 8787.\n\nAnd port 3001 returned `{\"error\":\"Not found\"}` which means it's running but the route doesn't exist at root.\n \nSo both Mission Control services are active on your Mac - the Vite frontend on 8787 and the API server on whatever port it uses. These are persistent launch agents that run whenever your machine is on. Meanwhile, the OpenClaw Gateway is consuming 108% CPU with 5.2GB memory, which is the real bottleneck here.\n\nLooking at what else is running, there are multiple agents (main, emmy, rex) all keeping 50% token context cached, plus Rex is spawning numerous subagents. The main issue is that with an 8GB MacBook Air, this setup is fundamentally constrained - the OpenClaw gateway itself is taking up over half your available memory, and that's before accounting for the OS and other processes.\n\nThe most impactful fix would be disabling Rex's automatic subagent creation since those are consuming memory even when idle, though there's also the question of whether Mission Control's services are actually being used or if they're just running unnecessarily in the background. -consuming. Let me ask Bobby about what he actually uses.\n\nActually, let me think about what's most actionable:\n\n1. **OpenClaw memory** — 5.2% RAM isn't terrible, but combined with swap pressure it's problematic\n2. **Mission Control** — Two Node.js servers running 24/7 on an 8GB MacBook Air. Are they being used?\n3. **Chrome tabs** — Chrome is using 0.9% RAM which is negligible\n4. **Rex subagents** — This is a big one. Multiple large-context sessions are expensive\n5. **Session cache** — 50% cached tokens for 10 sessions = a lot of memory\n\nI should ask Bobby if he's actually using Mission Control right now. If not, those services could be stopped to free up resources.\n","thinkingSignature":"2e2aaf98aa297addb8d662839dde9ce48ef9d30337317c746f03bbbb77fa2195"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nHere's what I found:\n\n**Running 24/7 on your Mac:**\n\n| Service | CPU | RAM | Purpose |\n|---------|-----|-----|---------|\n| **OpenClaw Gateway** | 108% (!) | 5.2% | Core AI system |\n| **MC Vite (port 8787)** | ~0% | tiny | Mission Control web UI |\n| **MC API Server** | ~0% | tiny | Mission Control backend |\n| **OpenClaw Node** | ~0% | 0.2% | Mobile/desktop connectivity |\n| **Ollama** | ~0% | tiny | Local model runner (not actively used) |\n\n**The real issue:** That **108% CPU on OpenClaw Gateway** is the big problem — it's been running since 6:42 AM and is hammering your Mac. Combined with your 8GB RAM limit, it's pushing into swap constantly.\n\n**A few questions:**\n\n1. **Do you actively use the Mission Control web UI** (the dashboard at port 8787)? If not, those two services are just wasting resources.\n\n2. **Rex (your research agent)** has been creating multiple subagents with large token caches — that's eating memory. Want me to tell him to be more conservative?\n\n3. **Your session cache is set to 50%** — which means 10 sessions all keeping ~100k tokens in memory. That's *a lot* on 8GB. We could drop cache to 25% to reduce memory pressure.\n\nThe biggest quick win would be **stopping Mission Control** if you don't use it — that's two Node.js servers running 24/7 for a web dashboard you might not need. Want me to check if it's actually being used?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":827,"output":879,"cacheRead":62464,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64170,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777737319409,"responseId":"06455167d6f843f62f2b1356b5702555"}}
