{"type":"message","id":"dcc93092","parentId":"79ff7266","timestamp":"2026-05-02T15:57:31.039Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is asking if stopping Mission Control will delete his data. I can confirm that stopping the LaunchAgents just stops the services - it doesn't delete any files, code, or data. Everything is preserved.\n","thinkingSignature":"a04b4faaa7bc87cfd7244644ac5a5ceac0d5b17071bef71cb8edb8f81ad71ac9"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nCorrect. Stopping it just stops the services — nothing gets deleted.\n\n- Files stay intact\n- Data stays intact\n- Settings stay intact\n- You can start it again anytime with `launchctl load`\n\nThink of it like closing an app vs deleting it. The code and data are all still there in `~/agent-mission-control/`, just not running in the background.\n\nWant me to stop it?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":63406,"output":126,"cacheRead":192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63724,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777737436293,"responseId":"064551dc1828a96219a11a3ba30d55d9"}}
