{"type":"message","id":"828e1bc5","parentId":"cf6ab7e1","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:02:45.810Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"These are respawning because they're managed by launchd and keepAlive is set to false (meaning it doesn't restart on exit, but since they're still running it keeps them going). The plists are disabled but the processes are still running as children of launchd.\n\nActually I think the issue is that the processes were started by launchd before the plists were disabled, and launchd is keeping them alive because it thinks they should be running. Let me try a different approach - find the PID and kill with prejudice, then also check if there's a parent launchd process that might be respawning.\n\nActually, looking more carefully - `Ss` means the process is in interruptible sleep (waiting for something), and the way these keep coming back suggests they're being started from somewhere else - maybe a script or something in the agent-mission-control directory.\n\n\nLet me check if there's an npm start script or something similar that might be triggering these processes.\n","thinkingSignature":"ea3742afe56e69609f118b84dadaeb41638e28eec9a0e2b54d9252624b759ff3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0yrmgapa15h0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/agent-mission-control/package.json | grep -A5 \"scripts\"","timeout":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0yrmgapa15h0_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ps aux | grep -E \"87247|87204\" | grep -v grep","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":254,"output":285,"cacheRead":66048,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66587,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777737753048,"responseId":"0645531953aeef5b5676feb0c9f4ca50"}}
