{"type":"message","id":"5926a99c","parentId":"66d30cb1","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:02:52.744Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I keep killing them but they keep restarting. The `serve-apps.cjs` seems to be auto-restarting them. Let me check what serve-apps.cjs does and if I can stop it, and also check what's spawning the mission-control processes.\n\nActually, `serve-apps.cjs` is what might be keeping them alive. Let me check what it does and kill that first, then kill the MC processes.\n","thinkingSignature":"647c51fd506c1f29ca581356daba76457c0301ee716004a276627a439eae9112"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n6yeyr9teajw_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/agent-mission-control/serve-apps.cjs | head -40","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":334,"output":133,"cacheRead":66240,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66707,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777737766085,"responseId":"0645532600b359a6a76a6b97a19a5b36"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d15e9f8b","parentId":"5926a99c","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:02:53.857Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_n6yeyr9teajw_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"const http = require('http')\nconst fs = require('fs')\nconst path = require('path')\n\nconst SERVERS = {\n  8787: { root: path.join(__dirname, 'dist'), defaultFile: 'index.html', name: 'Mission Control' },\n  8788: { root: path.join(__dirname, 'dist'), defaultFile: 'agent.html', name: 'Agent Chat' },\n  8789: { root: path.join(__dirname, 'recipe-rip'), defaultFile: 'index.html', name: 'Recipe Rip' },\n}\n\nObject.entries(SERVERS).forEach(([port, config]) => {\n  http.createServer((req, res) => {\n    let urlPath = req.url.split('?')[0]\n    let query = req.url.includes('?') ? req.url.substring(urlPath.length) : ''\n    let url = urlPath\n    \n    // Proxy /tools, /api, and /recipe-images to gateway\n    if (url.startsWith('/tools') || url.startsWith('/api') || url.startsWith('/recipe-images')) {\n      url = urlPath + query  // preserve query string for API\n      const proxyPort = url.startsWith('/api') ? 3001 : 18789\n      const bearer = url.startsWith('/tools') ? '286caba2a7d072f065abdec6f5cff840c2c31eb8f7801111' : ''\n      const options = {\n        hostname: 'localhost',\n        port: proxyPort,\n        path: url,\n        method: req.method,\n        headers: {\n          'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n          'Origin': `http://localhost:${port}`,\n        }\n      }\n      if (bearer) options.headers['Authorization'] = `Bearer ${bearer}`\n      \n      const proxyReq = http.request(options, (proxyRes) => {\n        res.writeHead(proxyRes.statusCode, {\n          ...proxyRes.headers,\n          'Access-Control-Allow-Origin': '*',\n        })\n        proxyRes.pipe(res)\n      })"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1062,"aggregated":"const http = require('http')\nconst fs = require('fs')\nconst path = require('path')\n\nconst SERVERS = {\n  8787: { root: path.join(__dirname, 'dist'), defaultFile: 'index.html', name: 'Mission Control' },\n  8788: { root: path.join(__dirname, 'dist'), defaultFile: 'agent.html', name: 'Agent Chat' },\n  8789: { root: path.join(__dirname, 'recipe-rip'), defaultFile: 'index.html', name: 'Recipe Rip' },\n}\n\nObject.entries(SERVERS).forEach(([port, config]) => {\n  http.createServer((req, res) => {\n    let urlPath = req.url.split('?')[0]\n    let query = req.url.includes('?') ? req.url.substring(urlPath.length) : ''\n    let url = urlPath\n    \n    // Proxy /tools, /api, and /recipe-images to gateway\n    if (url.startsWith('/tools') || url.startsWith('/api') || url.startsWith('/recipe-images')) {\n      url = urlPath + query  // preserve query string for API\n      const proxyPort = url.startsWith('/api') ? 3001 : 18789\n      const bearer = url.startsWith('/tools') ? '286caba2a7d072f065abdec6f5cff840c2c31eb8f7801111' : ''\n      const options = {\n        hostname: 'localhost',\n        port: proxyPort,\n        path: url,\n        method: req.method,\n        headers: {\n          'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n          'Origin': `http://localhost:${port}`,\n        }\n      }\n      if (bearer) options.headers['Authorization'] = `Bearer ${bearer}`\n      \n      const proxyReq = http.request(options, (proxyRes) => {\n        res.writeHead(proxyRes.statusCode, {\n          ...proxyRes.headers,\n          'Access-Control-Allow-Origin': '*',\n        })\n        proxyRes.pipe(res)\n      })","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777737773857}}
{"type":"message","id":"3146e87a","parentId":"d15e9f8b","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:03:09.433Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `serve-apps.cjs` is a custom server that serves Mission Control on ports 8787, 8788, 8789. It's separate from the LaunchAgents - the plists were calling it but even after we disabled the plists, something else is starting these processes.\n\nLet me check the data directory and the MC watchdog cron - maybe it's restarting MC every few minutes.\n\nActually, looking at the task history I saw earlier, there was a \"MC Watchdog\" cron job that was firing every 5 minutes and sending \"✅ MC OK\" messages to Telegram. That cron was running a shell command that called Cody (agent:cody) to do something. \n\nNow I'm digging into the MC watchdog cron job and finding the actual cron ID - it's `4a078218-10ea-45b4-b42b-66bddea0bd0a`. But it's already marked as disabled in the cron list I reviewed earlier. Let me trace back through the task history to understand what it was actually executing.\n","thinkingSignature":"e9eca37c47823975dc9b0e19dd87cfddd0a49bbef5f0f3a49628170374128463"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hns68j4945a4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron list --all 2>&1 | grep -E \"watchdog|MC|mission\" -i","timeout":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hns68j4945a4_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw tasks list 2>&1 | grep -i \"mission\\|watchdog\\|mc\" | tail -20","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":509,"output":318,"cacheRead":66560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67387,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777737773858,"responseId":"0645532dad1e5a97f31deb1818c2c078"}}
