{"type":"message","id":"07700c11","parentId":"be12a0f8","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:03:36.943Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me just kill the process and prevent it from restarting. The plists are already disabled. But it seems to restart itself. Let me check if there's a launch agent for it that gets triggered by launchd.\n\nActually, looking at the state: `Ss` means the process has been stopped/killed but the shell script that launched it still has children. Actually `Ss` means \"interruptible sleep\" with session leader. Let me just kill the session.\n\nActually let me just do a more aggressive kill.\n","thinkingSignature":"d1a35f287e49f390e4f4000a56ff2641b301f7ece2be013ff5a88d915fdf18b4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_a356enz7mwno_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"kill -9 87247 87204 2>/dev/null; pkill -f \"mission-control-api\" 2>/dev/null; pkill -f \"serve-apps\" 2>/dev/null; sleep 3; ps aux | grep -E \"mission-control|serve-apps\" | grep -v grep; echo \"Check complete\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":579,"output":208,"cacheRead":68032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68819,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777737808745,"responseId":"0645535003b2fbacc2785c337f493248"}}
