{"type":"message","id":"533a829f","parentId":"e35bed74","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:14:19.549Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_mr0z86vvfmsw_1","toolName":"image","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on the Activity Monitor screenshot provided, here are the top processes.\n\n**Important Note:** The screenshot shows the **Memory** tab. Therefore, **CPU % usage is not visible** in this image. The processes are listed below in order of their memory usage as shown in the screenshot.\n\n### Processes by Memory Usage\n\n| Process Name | Memory Usage |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **node** | 1.49 GB |\n| **openclaw-node** | 654.4 MB |\n| **Google Chrome Helper (Renderer)** | 363.7 MB |\n| **identityservicesd** | 280.5 MB |\n| **Safari** | 272.2 MB |\n| **Telegram** | 246.8 MB |\n| **Control Center** | 230.5 MB |\n| **distnoted** | 225.8 MB |\n| **Spotlight** | 203.0 MB |\n| **Notification Center** | 193.6 MB |\n| **Google Chrome** | 172.4 MB |\n| **Xcode** | 171.7 MB |\n| **python3.11** | 171.6 MB |\n| **python3.11** | 162.9 MB |\n| **IPNExtension** | 128.4 MB |\n| **Finder** | 117.0 MB |\n| **chrome-devtools-mcp** | 103.4 MB |\n| **remotepairingd** | 102.6 MB |\n\n---\n\n### System Memory Summary (at time of screenshot)\n\n*   **Physical Memory:** 8.00 GB\n*   **Memory Used:** 6.81 GB\n*   **Cached Files:** 1.15 GB\n*   **Swap Used:** 2.65 GB\n*   **Memory Pressure:** Stable (Green)"}],"details":{"model":"minimax-portal/MiniMax-VL-01","image":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/media/inbound/Screenshot_2026-05-02_at_12.10.34_PM---0a186acf-d5f9-4fcb-9cef-ab3344272397.png","attempts":[{"provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.5","error":"image description timed out after 1ms | image description timed out after 1ms"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777738459549}}
{"type":"message","id":"e7274c6f","parentId":"533a829f","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:14:41.373Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the full picture:\n\n**Memory usage breakdown:**\n- **node (OpenClaw Gateway)** — 1.49 GB\n- **openclaw-node** — 654 MB\n- **Google Chrome Helper** — 363 MB\n- **Safari** — 272 MB\n- **Telegram** — 246 MB\n- **Control Center** — 230 MB\n- **distnoted** — 225 MB\n- **Spotlight** — 203 MB\n- **Notification Center** — 193 MB\n- **Google Chrome** — 172 MB\n- **Xcode** — 171 MB\n- **python3.11** — 171 + 162 = 333 MB (two processes!)\n\n\n- **chrome-devtools-mcp** — 103 MB\n- **remotepairingd** — 102 MB\n\nThe memory pressure is green and stable at 6.81 GB used out of 8 GB, which is reassuring. But the real problem is that 2.65 GB swap being used — that's the culprit behind the slowdown. If I add up the major players, OpenClaw alone is consuming over 2.1 GB, Chrome and its helpers are around 535 MB, and Apple system processes like Control Center, distnoted, Spotlight, and Notification Center are collectively taking significant memory too.\n\nWhat's concerning is that Xcode is sitting there with 171 MB despite supposedly being closed, and those two python3.11 instances are using 333 MB combined — something's clearly running them in the background. The system is within its 8 GB physical limit, but the sheer number of processes competing for resources is what's creating the pressure.\n\nThe real problem isn't memory exhaustion itself — it's that the 8 GB MacBook Air was never meant to handle this workload continuously. The swap usage confirms the system is offloading less frequently accessed memory to disk, which is why things feel sluggish even though we're not technically hitting a wall. The path forward isn't necessarily adding more RAM — it's identifying which background processes are actually necessary versus which ones are just eating resources.\n","thinkingSignature":"082eb0491b2f9bc6b01dcf67981360a5c8fec80fd55ef6a45c0f8ca2875e19a9"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nNow I can see the full picture. Your memory is actually **stable (green)** — 6.81 GB used out of 8 GB. That's not the problem.\n\nHere's the real breakdown:\n\n**What's eating your RAM:**\n| Process | Memory | Problem? |\n|---------|--------|----------|\n| node (OpenClaw Gateway) | **1.49 GB** | High but normal for an AI system |\n| openclaw-node | **654 MB** | OK |\n| Chrome + Helpers | **535 MB** | About 50 Chrome tabs worth |\n| Safari | 272 MB | You have Safari open |\n| Telegram | 246 MB | Normal |\n| Control Center | 230 MB | High — often means a hanging process |\n| distnoted | 225 MB | High — macOS notification hub |\n| Spotlight | 203 MB | Indexing something? |\n| python3.11 x2 | **333 MB** | Something running Python in background |\n| Xcode | 171 MB | This should be 0 if closed |\n| chrome-devtools-mcp | 103 MB | The Chrome DevTools MCP server |\n\n**The swap (2.65 GB)** is what's making things feel slow — macOS is moving less-used memory to disk. With 8GB, you don't have much headroom.\n\n**What's NOT the problem:** Memory pressure is green. Your Mac isn't OOM or panicking — it's just working hard.\n\n**What would actually help:**\n1. Close Xcode if you don't need it (171 MB just sitting there)\n2. The python processes — something's running Python in the background. Could be the weather script or another automation\n3. Those two node processes (1.49 GB + 654 MB) are always going to be large on 8GB — that's just OpenClaw running\n\n**Honestly Bobby — with 8GB and this workload, some slowness is expected.** We removed the MC watchdog which was the biggest offender. The remaining services are all necessary ones. You might just need to accept that this MacBook Air has limits with what you're asking it to run 24/7."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":74356,"output":867,"cacheRead":128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75351,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777738459552,"responseId":"064555dbd52828e670ee2949e55f01a7"}}
