{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:8212808444\",\n  \"message_id\": \"24411\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"sender\": \"B G\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-05-02 12:19 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"B G (8212808444)\",\n  \"id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"name\": \"B G\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"8c746ac8","parentId":"685de763","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:19:29.185Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"1aff2e9a","parentId":"8c746ac8","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:19:46.279Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is asking if there's more cleanup to do. Let me think about what could still be cleaned up:\n\n1. Those python3.11 processes - what are they running? Could be weather scripts or other automations\n2. Xcode - should be 0 if closed\n3. The chrome-devtools-mcp - this is the Chrome DevTools Model Context Protocol server that's been running since April 22, consuming 103 MB\n\nLet me suggest a few more cleanup options and ask Bobby what he wants to do.\n","thinkingSignature":"345cff18c978f8fe864b6dadabc4856cbde762c18fde163d9f9b5990ed04d94e"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThere's a few things we *could* clean up, but they're minor:\n\n1. **Xcode (171 MB)** — if it's open and you're not using it, close it\n2. **chrome-devtools-mcp (103 MB)** — this is a Chrome extension helper running since April 22. If you don't use Chrome devtools for debugging, you could quit it\n3. **Those two python3.11 processes (333 MB)** — something is running Python. Could be a stuck automation or a script that didn't exit properly\n\n**To clean those up:**\n- Quit Xcode if open\n- Quit Chrome → reopen (this kills chrome-devtools-mcp)\n- The Python processes would require investigation to know what's running them\n\n**But here's the honest take:** Even if we cleaned all of those up, you'd free maybe 600 MB. Your OpenClaw team (1.49 GB + 654 MB) would still be ~2.1 GB. That's 27% of your RAM just for OpenClaw, which is always going to be the biggest resident.\n\nWant me to dig into what those Python processes are doing? Or are you ok with the current state — memory pressure is green, no swap storm, things running stable. We removed the main culprits (MC watchdog, MC services)."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":74280,"output":372,"cacheRead":320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalToke