ilt with Apple clang version 17.0.0 (clang-1700.6.3.2)\n  configuration: --prefix=/opt/homebrew/Cellar/ffmpeg/8.0.1_4 --enable-shared --enable-pthreads --enable-version3 --cc=clang --host-cflags= --host-ldflags= --enable-ffplay --enable-gpl --enable-libsvtav1 --enable-libopus --enable-libx264 --enable-libmp3lame --enable-libdav1d --enable-libvpx --enable-libx265 --enable-openssl --enable-videotoolbox --enable-audiotoolbox --enable-neon\n  libavutil      60.  8.100 / 60.  8.100\n  libavcodec     62. 11.100 / 62. 11.100\n  libavformat    62.  3.100 / 62.  3.100\n  libavdevice    62.  1.100 / 62.  1.100\n  libavfilter    11.  4.100 / 11.  4.100\n  libswscale      9.  1.100 /  9.  1.100\n  libswresample   6.  1.100 /  6.  1.100\n[aist#0:0/pcm_s16be @ 0xb46c14180] Guessed Channel Layout: mono\nInput #0, aiff, from '/tmp/section1_part1.aiff':\n  Duration: 00:01:14.30, start: 0.000000, bitrate: 353 kb/s\n  Stream #0:0: Audio: pcm_s16be (twos / 0x736F7774), 22050 Hz, mono, s16, 352 kb/s\nStream mapping:\n  Stream #0:0 -> #0:0 (pcm_s16be (native) -> mp3 (libmp3lame))\nPress [q] to stop, [?] for help\nOutput #0, mp3, to '/tmp/section1_part1.mp3':\n  Metadata:\n    TSSE            : Lavf62.3.100\n  Stream #0:0: Audio: mp3, 22050 Hz, mono, s16p\n    Metadata:\n      encoder         : Lavc62.11.100 libmp3lame\n[out#0/mp3 @ 0xb47024180] video:0KiB audio:291KiB subtitle:0KiB other streams:0KiB global headers:0KiB muxing overhead: 0.075971%\nsize=     291KiB time=00:01:14.29 bitrate=  32.1kbits/s speed= 352x elapsed=0:00:00.21    \nPart 1 done","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777739556896}}
{"type":"message","id":"24ad08be","parentId":"7bf78a5f","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:32:43.105Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, part 1 is done. Now let me continue with part 2 and the rest of section 1.","thinkingSignature":"1c8ee4f735dd42e3ba295e00513a6357c283852190f254f8429a1291dd9e4516"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hofst01nnqnp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"say -v 'Samantha' \"Why I Wrote This Guide\n\nI spent weeks figuring OpenClaw out on my own. Googling errors, watching YouTube videos, reading half-finished docs, starting over multiple times. There wasn't one place that said 'hey, here's exactly how to go from zero to having your own AI assistant running your life.'\n\nSo I built that place. This guide is everything I learned, everything I wish someone had told me, and everything I actually use day to day. No fluff, no theory — just real world, from someone who isn't a coder.\n\nIf you're working full time and want an AI assistant that actually works for you — not just for fun experiments — this guide is for you.\n\nBefore OpenClaw vs. After\n\nBefore: Every morning started the same way — I'd open my phone, check the weather, scroll through emails, check my calendar, look up what I had coming up. It was manual. Repetitive. And by the time I was done with all that, my brain was already tired before I even started working.\n\nI'd forget things. Appointments I'd lose track of. Bills I'd almost miss. Follow-ups that slipped through the cracks. I was managing my life with sticky notes and memory and anxiety. My files were a mess. Downloads went somewhere, I never knew where. Everything was scattered.\n\nAfter: I wake up and OpenClaw has already checked everything — my weather, my calendar, what's coming up today, any urgent emails. By the time I sit down, I'm already informed. No scrolling, no checking, no friction. It reminds me. It checks things. It handles the tracking so I don't have to hold it all in my head. My bills get tracked. My schedule gets monitored. The mental load shifted off my shoulders and onto the system.\" -o /tmp/section1_part2.aiff && ffmpeg -i /tmp/section1_part2.aiff /tmp/section1_part2.mp3 -y && cp /tmp/section1_part2.mp3 ~/.openclaw/media/section1_part2.mp3 && echo \"Part 2 done\"","timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1059,"output":494,"cacheRead":89952,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91505,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777739556899,"responseId":"06455a24b6f3772778e1cdb023fec6e5"}}
