{"type":"message","id":"ce95946d","parentId":"eb1f60d2","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:36:09.907Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is frustrated because he keeps having to correct me about the voice for voice memos. He wants me to use the macOS system default voice (no -v flag) for all voice memos. Let me update the TOOLS.md file to make this permanent.\n","thinkingSignature":"33eb2926107f38a5dbdac0f19f2eb5dc57f06e5928e9f85ca2636ac5bfcd8173"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oyl8yh6ra0gt_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"### Voice Memos (System Voice)\n- **Voice:** System default — no `-v` flag, no voice specification. Always use this for voice memos to Bobby.\n- **Format:** MP3 — always convert with ffmpeg: `say \"text\" -o /tmp/voice.aiff && ffmpeg -i /tmp/voice.aiff /tmp/voice.mp3 -y`\n- **Send:** Use message tool with `asVoice: true` and `filePath` pointing to the MP3\n- **IMPORTANT:** Never specify a voice with `-v` for voice memos — always use system default. Bobby does not want any other voice used.","oldText":"### Voice Memos (System Voice)\n- **Format:** MP3 — always convert with ffmpeg: `say \"text\" -o /tmp/voice.aiff && ffmpeg -i /tmp/voice.aiff /tmp/voice.mp3 -y`\n- **Voice:** System default — no `-v` flag, no voice specification\n- **Send:** Use message tool with `asVoice: true` and `filePath` pointing to the MP3\n- **Always test first** if unsure whether it worked"}],"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/TOOLS.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":96152,"output":363,"cacheRead":128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":96643,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777739754064,"responseId":"06455aea821dbabae29661716b151c56"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4fb69608","parentId":"ce95946d","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:36:10.461Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_oyl8yh6ra0gt_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in ~/.openclaw/workspace/TOOLS.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 160   - NEVER use presentation blocks with `url` fields — the Telegram plugin doesn't support URL buttons (only callback_data buttons)\n 161   - To send a clickable link: use HTML anchor tag format\n 162 \n 163 ### Voice Memos (System Voice)\n+164 - **Voice:** System default — no `-v` flag, no voice specification. Always use this for voice memos to Bobby.\n 164 - **Format:** MP3 — always convert with ffmpeg: `say \"text\" -o /tmp/voice.aiff && ffmpeg -i /tmp/voice.aiff /tmp/voice.mp3 -y`\n-165 - **Voice:** System default — no `-v` flag, no voice specification\n 166 - **Send:** Use message tool with `asVoice: true` and `filePath` pointing to the MP3\n-167 - **Always test first** if unsure whether it worked\n+167 - **IMPORTANT:** Never specify a voice with `-v` for voice memos — always use system default. Bobby does not want any other voice used.\n 168 \n 169 ### When Bobby Reports a Problem\n 170 - **ALWAYS correct it immediately** when he flags an issue\n 171 - Don't wait, don't explain why it happened — just fix it\n     ...","firstChangedLine":164},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777739770461}}
{"type":"message","id":"e5ed4687","parentId":"4fb69608","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:36:18.571Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Done. Updated TOOLS.md to make it clear: system default voice only, no -v flag, never specify a different voice.\n","thinkingSignature":"8abb1558a93ac366588a0c7e90231a2821de0304de4dd84727fa0c9a91e6c773"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nUpdated TOOLS.md — system default voice only, no `-v` flag, no exceptions. Won't happen again Bobby."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":428,"output":54,"cacheRead":96192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":96674,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777739770463,"responseId":"06455afb23ac1375a3da7ecbc6f69f58"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5bea2bf1","parentId":"e5ed4687","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:37:13.720Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"okay so please resend the voice memo of section 1 from the openlaw guide we have been working on so i can read along as i listen WITH THE CORRECT VOICE"}],"timestamp":1777739833606}}
{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:8212808444\",\n  \"message_id\": \"24423\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"sender\": \"B G\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-05-02 12:36 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"B G (8212808444)\",\n  \"id\": \"8212808444\",\n  \"name\": \"B G\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"a3db4d24","parentId":"5bea2bf1","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:37:13.721Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"e96787dd","parentId":"a3db4d24","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:37:35.778Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants me to resend Section 1 audio with the correct system default voice. Let me generate the audio files again but this time WITHOUT specifying a voice (no -v flag).\n","thinkingSignature":"08d7cc0483d3068011aedecb27641da6d245fc7d8356c58cf30de910825c2915"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_knhewkvumb8c_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"say \"Section 1: What is OpenClaw? OpenClaw is an autonomous AI agent that runs on your computer — think of it like having a digital employee who lives on your MacBook. It's always working, always monitoring, always ready to help. Unlike ChatGPT where you open it, ask a question, close it, and it's gone — OpenClaw stays running in the background. It checks your email, manages your files, runs automations, sends you updates, and handles all the repetitive stuff you'd otherwise have to do yourself.\n\nHere's what makes it different from other AI tools:\n\nIt's local. OpenClaw runs on your own machine, not in some distant data center. Your data stays on your computer. Your memories are stored in simple text files you can actually read and understand.\n\nIt's always on. It doesn't wait for you to ask. It monitors, reminds, checks, and coordinates throughout the day. You set up workflows once, and they run on their own.\n\nIt's built around open-source. OpenClaw started as a side project from one developer, and it grew into one of the fastest-growing open-source projects in history.\n\nIt works with tools you already use. Email, calendar, reminders, files, browsers, messaging apps — OpenClaw connects to them all.\" -o /tmp/s1p1.aiff && ffmpeg -i /tmp/s1p1.aiff /tmp/s1p1.mp3 -y && echo done","timeout":60}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_knhewkvumb8c_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"say \"The Story Behind OpenClaw\n\nOpenClaw was created by Peter Steinberger, an Austrian developer who spent 13 years building PSPDFKit — a PDF company that ended up powering document handling on over a billion devices. We're talking Apple, Dropbox, all the big players. In 2023, he sold that company for reportedly around 110 million dollars. By all accounts, he made it. He was done. Retired.\n\nExcept... he wasn't really done. He was burned out.\n\nI felt like Austin Powers where they suck the mojo out. Peter told Lex Fridman in an interview. I couldn't get code out anymore. I was just, like, staring and feeling empty.\n\nSo he did what any burnt-out tech millionaire would do — he traveled. Partied. Tried therapy. Nothing stuck. He was looking for meaning and couldn't find it.\n\nThen in April 2025, something changed. He was tinkering with a Twitter analysis tool and realized AI had shifted. The tools could finally handle the boring parts of coding, leaving him free to just build. So he got back in the game.\n\nHe built the first prototype of OpenClaw in just one hour. His 44th AI project since 2009. And he created it for the simplest reason possible — I was annoyed that it didn't exist, so I just prompted it into existence.\n\nThe project went through a few names before settling on OpenClaw. First it was Clawdbot, then Moltbot, then OpenClaw — all because of naming disputes with other companies. Anthropic had trademark issues with Molt. It launched quietly in late 2025 and then exploded.\n\nWe're talking 2 million visitors in a single week. Over 180,000 GitHub stars in just a few weeks. One of the fastest-growing open-source projects in history.\n\nPeter caught the attention of every big player in tech. Sam Altman called him a genius. Mark Zuckerberg personally reached out to recruit him. OpenAI hired him in February 2026. But here's the thing — Peter made sure OpenClaw stayed open-source and community-driven, moving it into an independent foundation supported by OpenAI. He didn't sell out.\n\nI don't do this for the money. He told Fridman. I want to have fun and have impact.\n\nThat's the vibe behind OpenClaw. It's not some corporate AI tool. It's a side project from a developer who was bored and wanted to build something useful. And it grew into something that changed how a lot of us think about what our computers can actually do.\" -o /tmp/s1p2.aiff && ffmpeg -i /tmp/s1p2.aiff /tmp/s1p2.mp3 -y && echo done","timeout":90}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":96543,"output":959,"cacheRead":224,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":97726,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777739833721,"responseId":"06455b3ad8c4bf9e1777088fe2db2ce2"}}
