{"type":"message","id":"a037f307","parentId":"9cbc3348","timestamp":"2026-05-02T16:46:22.756Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to split this into parts that fit within say limits. Each `say` command can handle a good chunk. Let me split it into natural chunks - maybe 4-5 parts based on the section structure:\n\nPart 1: Title + Story Behind OpenClaw (intro + Peter Steinberger story)\nPart 2: Why I Wrote This Guide + Before OpenClaw vs After\nPart 3: What OpenClaw Actually Does\nPart 4: What OpenClaw is NOT + My Agent Team + ending\n\nLet me calculate approximate sizes. 7259 chars total, let's split at natural breaks.\n","thinkingSignature":"741f324b9bb204aab7e6e08d382e941aac0ff9f931a651bba20f0b6ebe7edb55"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_blowbv11xcee_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Part 1: Title + Story Behind OpenClaw (up to \"That's the vibe...\")\nsed -n '1,/That's the vibe behind OpenClaw/p' /tmp/s1_clean.txt | sed '$ d' > /tmp/s1a.txt\n# Part 2: Why I Wrote This Guide + Before/After\nsed -n '/Why I Wrote This Guide/,/What OpenClaw Actually Does/p' /tmp/s1_clean.txt | head -c 2000 > /tmp/s1b.txt\n# Part 3: What OpenClaw Actually Does\nsed -n '/What OpenClaw Actually Does/,/What OpenClaw is NOT/p' /tmp/s1_clean.txt | sed '$ d' > /tmp/s1c.txt\n# Part 4: What OpenClaw is NOT + My Agent Team + Complete\nsed -n '/What OpenClaw is NOT/,$p' /tmp/s1_clean.txt > /tmp/s1d.txt\n\nwc -c /tmp/s1a.txt /tmp/s1b.txt /tmp/s1c.txt /tmp/s1d.txt","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":187,"output":397,"cacheRead":114560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":115144,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777740368202,"responseId":"06455d503a2bcf278e8f207d41950cb4"}}
