{"type":"message","id":"dc99f569","parentId":"5ef6ffd6","timestamp":"2026-05-02T18:54:40.613Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is saying he received a morning brief message from me. But I didn't send a morning brief - I just sent the Section 1 audio from the OpenClaw Guide. \n\nWait, this message is the \"☀️ Morning Brief\" message from this morning. But I just sent Section 1 audio. This morning brief must have been sent earlier by a cron job (Morning Brief cron job) and Bobby is seeing it now, or it's showing up in the chat.\n\nActually, looking at the message - \"Morning Brief had a timeout error this morning\" - this morning brief cron job must have fired and sent this message. But I didn't send this myself. This was sent by the Morning Brief cron job that failed earlier.\n\n\nLet me double-check what's actually happening here before responding. the message appears in the conversation, someone else must have sent it or it was delivered through another channel. But I'm confused because I didn't send it just now, and the cron job shouldn't fire again until 5:30 AM tomorrow.\n\nI'm realizing this might be a timing issue with how the cron job delivers messages—maybe the system sent a notification about the earlier failure, or there's a scheduled task that fires periodically to recap failures. Either way, I should clarify that this wasn't something I initiated in this conversation.\n\nLooking at my session labels, the main agent is `agent:main:main` and the Telegram one is `agent:main:telegram:direct:82128...`, so I have multiple sessions running. I never actually sent a morning brief message this session—I only sent the audio for Section 1—so this message must have come from the cron job system or an automated delivery that's separate from what I was doing.\n\nBut wait, that doesn't make sense. The cron job runs in an isolated subagent session and delivers via Telegram, so how would it appear in my current chat session? Unless the Telegram plugin is displaying the message in both the cron delivery channel and my current session as a unified conversation view. Or maybe Bobby is forwarding me a message he received elsewhere. I should just ask him directly to clarify where this came from.\n\nActually, looking back at the timeline—the morning brief cron fired at 5:30 AM and timed out, Bobby sent me a message at 2:54 PM asking about it, then asked about sessions again at 3:07 PM, then around 3:12 PM we moved into OpenClaw guide work where he asked for Section 1. So this morning brief failure message must have come through earlier in our session before we pivoted to the guide work. But I didn't send that message in this current conversation, so either it's from a previous session or I'm misremembering the timeline.\n\nGiven that the message has the exact format of the Morning Brief cron job that we discussed earlier when listing cron jobs, I'm thinking this might be from an older iteration of my system prompt that Bobby is referencing, or the message is appearing in a consolidated chat view across sessions, or Bobby is showing me something from a different platform entirely.\n\nLet me reconsider — could this be from a subagent or a cron job that ran in a different session? Looking at the cron job list, the Morning Brief job has `lastRunStatus: error`, so it definitely failed this morning. But I never actually sent the Morning Brief this session since we were focused on the OpenClaw guide work. If the cron job sent a message to Telegram saying \"☀️ Morning Brief had a timeout error,\" it would only show up in Telegram, not here. I'm getting confused about where this message is actually appearing.\n\nLet me just ask Bobby directly where he saw this message and what triggered it. I should just be straightforward and ask him directly — no need to overthink where the message came from or whether I sent it in a different context. The important thing is that the Morning Brief cron job did fail this morning as we discussed earlier, and now I want to understand if he's referring to a separate message he received or something from an earlier session.","thinkingSignature":"90edd48eac32722eb5a0324acce7072dfe98f64dd7b3423097ca6f8ad8c38aba"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nI didn't send that message this session — I only sent you the Section 1 audio for the OpenClaw Guide.\n\nThat message looks like the **Morning Brief cron job** that failed earlier. It was supposed to run at 5:30 AM but timed out (we discussed this earlier when I listed the cron jobs — it showed `lastRunStatus: error`).\n\nDid you receive it on **Telegram** separately? Cron jobs deliver to Telegram directly, so you might have gotten it there. Or are you seeing it somewhere else in the conversation?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":115615,"output":924,"cacheRead":352,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":116891,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777748062375,"responseId":"06457b5faf82fb8fa239f6c2361e3c05"}}
