{"type":"message","id":"d64fc202","parentId":"47692322","timestamp":"2026-05-02T23:42:11.196Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants something cheaper. Let me think about what actually costs money vs. what's free. Actually, most of what would actually help (RAM, CPU) can't be bought cheaply. But there are some things that are free or very cheap that might help:1. **Best Buy Gift Card** - give him something to put towards a future Mac Studio\n2. **Nothing** - honestly the upgrades that would actually help (RAM) aren't buyable for this machine\n\nOr maybe he just wants to browse Best Buy for fun. Let me keep it light and honest.","thinkingSignature":"7fb646e198a77f698b992a7a757f9756e6e898096e6930b55811f979155905c5"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nHonestly Bobby — the stuff that would actually fix the slowness (more RAM, better CPU) isn't something you can just grab at Best Buy for cheap. It's a hardware limitation of the MacBook Air.\n\n**Actually free/cheap things that DO help:**\n- Close Xcode and other apps you're not using (we mentioned this earlier)\n- Keep Chrome tabs minimal\n- Restart your Mac occasionally\n\n**If you want something just to treat yourself:**\n- Best Buy gift card for when you're ready to upgrade later\n- A cheap USB-C hub if you need one\n- External monitor if you don't have one — gives you breathing room on screen\n\nBut there's no $50 thing from Best Buy that's going to make OpenClaw fast on an 8GB Air. That's just the reality of hardware limits.\n\nWhat kind of stuff were you thinking? Maybe I can help put things in perspective."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":116020,"output":294,"cacheRead":352,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":116666,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777765322089,"responseId":"0645becb164badc3f80365c7b9878943"}}
