{"type":"message","id":"32c575e2","parentId":"a94ea75d","timestamp":"2026-05-02T23:44:24.896Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is asking about Meta glasses (Ray-Ban Meta smart glasses). These are smart glasses that can take photos, record video, play music, and have some AI capabilities. They have a Meta AI assistant built in.\n\nCan I use them? Not directly through OpenClaw. Let me think about this...\n\nThe Meta glasses have:\n- A built-in AI assistant (Meta AI)\n- Camera for photos/video\n- Audio for calls/music\n- Touch controls\n\nFor OpenClaw specifically - OpenClaw runs on a Mac, so Meta glasses aren't a direct input/output for OpenClaw. However, there are some potential use cases:\n\n1. **Voice memos** - You could record voice notes on the glasses and then I could transcribe them when you send them to me\n2. **Taking photos** - Send me photos from the glasses and I could analyze them\n3. **Voice commands** - Meta AI on the glasses, but that's separate from OpenClaw\n\nI can't directly connect Meta glasses to OpenClaw as a peripheral. They're separate systems. The glasses run Meta AI, not OpenClaw.\n\nHowever, Bobby might be thinking about this from a workflow perspective - like using the glasses for hands-free voice notes while he's out and about, then sending those to me to process.\n\nLet me be honest with him - I can't directly use Meta glasses, but they could be part of his workflow in other ways.\n","thinkingSignature":"23cb70f99dd2bc49a49827bb9e7d4d0cd18cce605ccd63e566e1340609c8ab40"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nNot directly — Meta glasses run Meta AI, not OpenClaw. They're separate systems.\n\n**What the Meta glasses could do for your workflow:**\n- Record voice memos hands-free → send to me → I transcribe/analyze\n- Take photos → send to me → I can describe what's in them\n- Make calls, listen to music\n\n**What they can't do:**\n- Replace your Mac for running OpenClaw agents\n- Connect to OpenClaw directly\n\n**A more useful cheap upgrade for OpenClaw:** If you have an old **iPhone sitting around**, you could use it as a dedicated device for voice notes — just speak to it, then send the recordings to me. No extra cost.\n\nBut honestly Bobby — if you want Meta glasses just to have them, they're cool. I just don't want you buying them thinking they'll make your OpenClaw setup faster. They won't."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":116116,"output":476,"cacheRead":320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":116912,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777765448971,"responseId":"0645bf498f011b57bd8eb490ebcce949"}}
