{"type":"message","id":"60e56837","parentId":"e7ff3a9e","timestamp":"2026-05-03T03:35:36.693Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is asking for help planning his day tomorrow. Let me figure out what he needs:\n\n1. Get 6 hours of sleep tonight\n2. Drink water with sea salt before bed (for electrolytes)\n3. DoorDash in the morning\n4. Make Logan breakfast\n5. Potentially stop at Kroger or Publix on the way back\n\nHe wants me to help him do all this AND get enough sleep. Let me think about what he needs to do tomorrow.\n\nHe probably needs to sleep by around midnight to get 6 hours before 6am or something. Let me help him plan this out.\n\nLet me think about what I can proactively do:\n- Set a reminder for him to drink water with sea salt before bed\n- Set a reminder for tomorrow morning (DoorDash, breakfast for Logan)\n\n\n- Check his calendar for anything scheduled\n- I could draft a DoorDash order message for him so it's ready to go, and brainstorm breakfast ideas that work with what he has available or might need to pick up\n\nI should just help him figure this out directly.\n","thinkingSignature":"1c06a29ddf78ee5a64326844b090fd8ed49f9bdb1fcbdf8146715f933146c826"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nBobby — here's what I'm thinking for tomorrow:\n\n**Tonight before bed:**\n- Water + sea salt — I'll remind you before you sleep\n\n**Tomorrow morning:**\n- DoorDash → I'll help you order whenever you're ready\n- Kroger/Publix stop → I can have a list ready of what you need for breakfast\n- Make Logan breakfast → I can find a recipe, give you instructions, whatever you need\n\n**What I need from you to make this smooth:**\n\n1. **What time do you want to wake up?** (so I can set alarms/reminders)\n2. **What does Logan usually eat for breakfast?** (so I know what to aim for)\n3. **DoorDash — what kind of food?** (breakfast, or something specific?)\n4. **How far is Kroger/Publix from your apartment?** (traffic/time)\n\nGive me those details and I'll set up a solid plan — reminders, grocery list, recipe options — the works. Then tomorrow morning you just wake up and execute, no thinking required."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":116722,"output":432,"cacheRead":128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":117282,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777779321410,"responseId":"0645f57ac241efc520cedb8711bc9072"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e9accc6f","parentId":"60e56837","timestamp":"2026-05-03T03:39:18.039Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"well given the current time, what would be the best time for me to go to bed? i think i want to make eggs with toast/rice and pick up some oranges and 100% pure fresh pressed apple juice for breakfast and we can also have coffee too. and for doordash i meant that i am going to be working as a dasher making money from doordash haha. i live at 1911 mobley way knoxville tn 37922 and kroger and publix are just right around the corner. i know i also want to work on the openclaw guide and try to get that close to finished or as close to finished as possible tomorrow. i also want to work on recipe rip and see if i cant start to get going on starting to sell it."}],"timestamp":1777779557916}}
