{"type":"message","id":"09f496ca","parentId":"ebb01cbe","timestamp":"2026-05-03T03:55:15.087Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is asking how I would set the alarm. He's probably curious about the mechanism. I can set a reminder using cron with an explicit timestamp. Let me explain the process and then ask if he wants me to set it.\n\nActually, based on TOOLS.md and MEMORY.md, I know the rule: use explicit ISO-8601 timestamps with `schedule.kind: \"at\"` — never cron expressions for one-shot reminders because of the timezone bug.\n\nCurrent time is May 2, 2026, ~12:20 PM EDT\n- Bed by 12:30 AM = May 3, 2026 04:30 UTC\n- Wake up at 6:30 AM = May 3, 2026 10:30 UTC\n\n\n- \nNow I'll explain the process to him and confirm he wants me to set these reminders before I proceed.","thinkingSignature":"2c5aaa62809d69a73ef971511e76c07c849ce288d855475b26124267397f1b43"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nI'd set it using a **scheduled reminder** that texts you directly on Telegram at the exact time. Here's how:\n\n**Tonight:**\n- **11:45 PM** → Reminder: \"Water + sea salt before bed 💧🧂\"\n- **12:30 AM** → Reminder: \"Time for bed! 🛏️\" (optional since you're going on your own)\n\n**Tomorrow:**\n- **6:30 AM** → Wake up alarm: \"☀️ Up! DoorDash starts soon. Coffee first.\"\n\nEach one is a one-shot reminder — fires once, delivers to your Telegram, done. No repeats, no complications.\n\nWant me to set them all now? I'll knock them out in 30 seconds."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":117613,"output":330,"cacheRead":128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":118071,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777780499395,"responseId":"0645fa13ed956695d8d22dc0f1a60a6c"}}
